begin_memory_text: We discussed school and where we were located. I asked her about her dorm/room and she explained her situation and how her school was set up.
middle_memory_text: We discussed the pandemic and also life in our respective states. Also discussed Hawaii a bit in regards to traveling there. We talked about the covid testing measures that were in place at our schools.
end_memory_text: We discussed our animals and had general conversations about our pets. We also discussed museums, as my partner wanted to do some work at museums possibly. I told her I had experience working there.
rest_of_day_open: I see my week going pretty well, all things considered. I hope to get some shopping done for an upcoming trip of mine that I'm excited about. I enjoy shopping in general so I'm looking forward to shopping later this week. There are also some people I hope to talk to later this week, which makes me excited.
critical_positive: I felt more comfortable off the bat because she was a young woman, like me. I think we were both more on the shy, artsy side of things so that made it easier to relate and converse, in my eyes. We were both also pretty good at responding to what the other was saying.
critical_negative: Since we were both a bit more shy, we had some moments of dead air. I don't think either of us really knew how to carry the conversation in those moments. It also felt like we were just trying to run out the clock at times, which sometimes made things feel more awkward.

begin_memory_text: We talked about what we are studying at school and how covid has affected both us and friends that we have. We covered what it is like trying to get a job right now, as well as being a freshman this year.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the differences between California where she is and New York, where I am. We discussed her plans to travel to Hawaii with her boyfriend soon. We also briefly talked about where we grew up.
end_memory_text: Her dog came onto the screen, and she was very cute. She was a ten-year-old toy poodle. She really likes toys of all kinds. We started talking about our current and past pets, and how both of our old shepherd dogs were much pickier about their preferred toys.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week is going to be very busy. I have two midterms to do on Monday and another one coming up on Wednesday. I will be trying to study and write some essays for most of the week. Hopefully, come Friday I can take a bit of a break.
critical_positive: It worked out that we were both around the same age, so we had many experiences in common. We were both able to talk about school and how covid was affecting our lives. We also were both asking a similar amount of questions, so the balance of the conversation worked out pretty well.
critical_negative: There were a couple of moments where there was a pause in the conversation where I couldn't think of anything to say or ask my partner. She always came around and asked me another question, but in those moments I felt like I was missing some beats in the conversation.
